# Framework Adapter Pattern

Every agent framework adapter must implement the `AgentAdapter` interface and be registered in the `AdapterRegistry`.

## File structure for a new adapter

```
src/enterprise/adapters/<framework>/
├── <framework>.adapter.ts        # AgentAdapter implementation
├── <framework>.adapter.spec.ts   # Tests
├── <framework>.models.ts         # Framework-specific types (optional)
└── index.ts                      # Public exports
```

## Implementation checklist

1. Implement `AgentAdapter` from `adapter.interface.ts`
2. Translate framework events to/from ADK `Event` model (from `src/app/core/models/types.ts`)
3. Declare capability support honestly (`supportsStreaming()`, `supportsTracing()`, etc.)
4. Register in `src/enterprise/adapters/registry.ts`
5. Add unit tests with mock HTTP responses
6. Handle errors gracefully — adapt framework-specific errors to a unified error format

## Event model translation

The upstream UI expects ADK `Event` objects. Your adapter must translate:

```typescript
// Framework response → ADK Event
function toAdkEvent(frameworkResponse: FrameworkResponse): Event {
  return {
    id: frameworkResponse.id,
    author: frameworkResponse.agent_name,
    content: { role: 'model', parts: [{ text: frameworkResponse.output }] },
    timestamp: frameworkResponse.created_at,
  };
}
```
